<PageTitle>Ignore Members</PageTitle>

<h1>Ignore Members</h1>

<p>Specific members can be excluded from automatic mapping by using the <code>ignoredMembers</code> parameter on the <code>Map</code> attribute.</p>

<p>Ignored members are never considered for automatic mapping even if configured by manual means.</p>

<CodeBlock Language="CodeLanguage.CSharp" EnableLineNumbers="true" Code=@Code />

<p>In this example, <code>Id</code> and <code>MiddleName</code> are excluded from the mapping.</p>

<h2>Scope</h2>

<p>Ignored members are scoped per mapping.</p>

<ul>
    <li>They apply only to the <code>Map&lt;TSource, TDestination&gt;</code> declaration on which they are defined</li>
    <li>Other mappings on the same mapper are unaffected</li>
</ul>

@code
{
    const string Code =
"""
[GenerateMapper]
[Map<User, UserDto>(ignoredMembers: [nameof(User.Id), nameof(User.MiddleName)])]
public partial class UserMapper;
""";
}